@hypebeastkicks: On the latest installment of 'What The Tech?' we sat down with @newlight_technologies’ CEO Mark Herrema to better understand the sustainability and discovery of AirCarbon, how it will change the future of Nike, footwear, and pretty much anything else it wants to tackle. Hit the link in bio for the full feature.⁠⁠
Photo: @nike/Newlight Technology

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by HYPEBEAST on September 17, 2021 tagging @nike, @newlight_technologies, and @hypebeastkicks. May be an image of footwear and text that says 'WHAT THE TECH? AIRCARBON HYPEBEAST'.

Photo by HYPEBEAST on September 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'IS IT NAIVE TO ASK HOW USING THE OCEAN'S MICROORGANISMS IS A SUSTAINABLE PROCESS? HOW DOES THIS ALL WORK? The molecule's technical name PHB (Polyhydroxybutyrate), almost all life makes it, you and humans, we make turns out that there are microorganisms the ocean that eat methane carbon dioxide as their food source, and when they do that, one the things that they make inside their cells kind like muscle the molecule PHB. When you extract that can turn into fine white powder and that is meltable, so now you have a replacement for things like plastic. HYPEBEAST'.

Photo by HYPEBEAST on September 17, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'HOW DO YOU ACTUALLY TAKE OUT THE MOLECULE AND THEN TURN IT INTO AIRCARBON? Eagle is our first production facility just outside of L.A., and that middle tank, think of like slice the ocean. It's big stainless steel tank filled with saltwater, and into that, we add these naturally occurring, not genetically modified, microorganisms. Into that, we add our gases which they eat their food source, themselves with PHB, and once that batch done goes inside our building and we basically push through a high-pressure filtration process. HYPEBEAST'.

Photo by HYPEBEAST on September 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'HAVE YOU FACED ANY CHALLENGES IN CHANGING PEOPLE'S MINDS OR MAKING FOOTWEAR AND FASHION MORE SUSTAINABLE? |think the industry is very eager to adopt sustainable pathways. The challenges have been getting scale. As much as company would love to work with you, you don't have enough product or you're not meeting performance targets... yeah. That was 18-year journey for us, was hard. From that point, the industry has been very receptive. HYPEBEAST'.

Photo by HYPEBEAST on September 17, 2021. May be an image of saddle-stitched leather and text that says 'A SHOE HAS Το BE FUNCTIONAL. IS AIRCARBON ADAPTABLE TO THESE NEEDS? The products we have on the market are demonstrative of that. You can get AirCarbon eyewear that's high-performance injection molded, and then you can get AirCarbon bags that have different functionality that also works well my wallet made from AirCarbon and works great, granted I'm not putting through F1 racing. HYPEBEAST'.

Photo by HYPEBEAST on September 17, 2021. May be an image of footwear and text that says 'FROM WHAT YOU'VE SHOWN ME AND EXPLAINED, IT LOOKS LIKE AIRCARBON COULD BE USED FOR A SOLE UNIT ON A SHOE. We re certainly going to be looking at that. The uppers, every component we can. The more AirCarbon we get in there, the lower the carbon footprint. HYPEBEAST'.

Photo by HYPEBEAST on September 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'DO YOU THINK AIRCARBON WILL BECOME MORE POPULAR AS WE LEARN MORE ABOUT HOW TO USE IT? I I think so. took us many years get into commercial-scale production and we finally have that. That happened last year when we brought Eagle online for the first time; now with Eagle online and commercial-scale capacity, we hope to be an increasingly important part of the fashion industry. HYPEBEAST'.
